data.title: Grand Duke Dmitri Pavlovich Romanov (1891
data.meta_description: Russian Royalty, Grand Duke of Russia. He was the only son (second child) of Grand Duke Paul Alexandrovich, the first cousin of the csar Nicholas II. His mother was  Alexandra Georgievna of Greece. He is well remembered for his role in the assasination of the holy man Rasputin in 1916 and later, after the revolution of...
